caption:
Here’s is the CRAZY fact of the day…🏆🤯

Every year since 2007/08, the winner of the UEFA Champions League has always been either:

‣ Real Madrid
‣ FC Barcelona
‣ Or a team that knocked out either Barcelona or Real Madrid

2024: Real Madrid
2023: Manchester City (eliminated Real Madrid)
2022: Real Madrid
2021: Chelsea (eliminated Real Madrid)
2020: Bayern Munich (eliminated Barcelona)
2019: Liverpool (eliminated Barcelona)
2018: Real Madrid
2017: Real Madrid
2016: Real Madrid
2015: Barcelona
2014: Real Madrid
2013: Bayern Munich (eliminated Barcelona)
2012: Chelsea (eliminated Barcelona)
2011: Barcelona
2010: Inter Milan (eliminated Barcelona)
2009: Barcelona
2008: Manchester United (eliminated Barcelona)

PSG didn’t face either Real Madrid or Barça this season…
Meanwhile, Inter knocked Barça out of the Champions League!

Will this trend continue? 👇
